title: The Clean Coder
author: Robert C. Martin
notes: Great insights on professional software development. The chapter on saying no was particularly valuable.

title: Design Patterns
author: Gang of Four
notes: Currently on the Observer pattern chapter. Taking notes on when to use each pattern.

title: System Design Interview
author: Alex Xu
notes: Essential for tech interviews. The database sharding section is complex but well explained.

title: React Native in Action
author: Nader Dabit
notes: Good introduction to React Native. Some sections are outdated but core concepts remain valid.

title: Refactoring
author: Martin Fowler
notes: Learning about code smells and when to refactor. The extract method technique is very useful.

title: You Don't Know JS
author: Kyle Simpson
notes: Deep dive into JavaScript fundamentals. The closures explanation finally clicked for me.

title: Clean Architecture
author: Robert C. Martin
notes: Understanding the principles of good architecture. The dependency rule is key.

title: The Algorithm Design Manual
author: Steven S. Skiena
notes: Working through the graph algorithms section. War stories are entertaining and educational.
